<div dir="ltr">
















<p class="MsoNormal">Hi Folks!!</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>

<p class="MsoNormal">We announced a bug fix release of Ushahidi, dubbed v2.7.4
last evening. We knocked out a couple of bugs and improvements such as:</p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li><span style>Password validation errors</span><br></li><li><span style>Runtime errors in settings and when submitting
reports</span><br></li><li><span style>Updating Openlayers to v2.13.1</span><br></li><li><span style>Addition of missing files during a fresh install</span></li></ul><p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">For a full run down of all the fixed bugs and improvements,
have a look at the <a href="https://github.com/ushahidi/Ushahidi_Web/issues?q=milestone%3Av2.7.4+is%3Aclosed">2.7.4
milestone on our github issues page</a>.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Crowdmap Classic should be updated to match this release by
6<sup>th</sup> August, 2014. Communication on this will be made once the update
is complete</p><p class="MsoNormal"> </p>

<p class="MsoNormal">A list of all plugins compatible with this version can be
found on <a href="mailto:https://wiki.ushahidi.com/display/WIKI/Plugin+Version+Compatibility">our
plugins compatibility wiki page</a>.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Thank </b><b>you!</b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>

<p class="MsoNormal">As always, this release happened with the help of our
greater community. Huge thanks to all of you who sent in those bug reports,
pull requests, translations, questions and comments. These went a long way in
making this release happen.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:15pt"><span style="color:black">Even as we move forward with development on v3,
we definitely encourage you to keep sending in those pull requests and sending
in your translation contributions on v2!!</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="color:black">Looking towards v3!</span></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:15pt"><span style="color:black">We’re getting closer and closer to launching the
new version of Ushahidi(v3), and want to make sure that what we envision
matches what you envision from the revamped platform.</span></p>

<ul type="disc">
 <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:black"><b><a href="https://drive.google.com/a/ushahidi.com/?ddrp=1#folders/0B5redy59hE0qbzRqNjRMYjF2RTQ"><span style="color:rgb(89,143,201);text-decoration:none">Community
     Paths</span></a></b>: We want to better understand how
     to meet your goals and expectations on v3 based on your experience with
     Ushahidi v2. We want to know how the tools helps or hinders you from
     achieving your deployment goals. Take a few minutes of your time this week
